                <note rend="inline" type="source">875.00/122: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tirana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-05-18T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1924</hi> [<hi rend="italic">—12
                            noon</hi>]</date>.<lb/>[Received 5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. My telegram number 40 of May 4, noon. …</p>
                <p>Arms are being distributed here to reserves and others. Movement on Scutari
                    planned for this week. A portion of Tirana garrison of doubtful loyalty. Should
                    south join rebels, which seems probable, telegraph lines would be cut. I
                    recommend that a destroyer be sent to Durazzo for communication purposes. Copy
                    to European Information Center.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
